"A russian research institute whose main activities are:
- research, development and production of automatic control systems and their functional devices for various military and civilian facilities;
- research and development of algorithms for stabilization, control, navigation, and guidance;
- development of small-sized onboard computers and related software.
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile system it develops and supplies AB-60IS (9B705) onboard control systems (BCS)."

"Manufacturer of electrical products for various industries, including:
- electromagnetic starters and contactors (PM12, PML-kze series for currents up to 250A)
- relays (intermediate relays, electrothermal current relays (RTT) for currents up to 330A);
- contact terminals and clamping units (BZK-40, BZK-54);
- spare parts (control coils, contact groups).
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of Orion UAVs it supplies inertial fuses IP-150 and IP-75M, which are part of the power supply system."

"As the so-called ""acting Minister of Culture of Zaporizhzhia region"", he contributes to the erasure of Ukrainian identity in the occupied territories, namely 
• called for ""countering the falsification of history and preserving the historical heritage of Russian values and ideals""; 
• promoted educational activities for cultural workers aimed at disseminating ""knowledge of the history of the fatherland at lectures of leading federal museums"", etc."

"Instrumentation and machine building enterprise. It is a part of the Tactical Rocketry Corporation.
Main products:
electronic systems for high-precision artillery, missile and anti-tank weapons;
radar homing heads for tactical guided missiles;
on-board thermal imaging and thermal imaging equipment;
optical-mechanical and optoelectronic products;
products for the aerospace industry;
electrical control equipment;
optics"

;"The transport and logistics operator, which is part of the military construction complex of the ministry of defence of the russian federation, delivers various cargoes by its own vessels in the waters of the Black and Mediterranean seas, the Baltic, the Arctic and the Far East, and its key competence is the transportation of military and special equipment, dangerous and project cargoes. 
In January 2016, the government of the russian federation appointed Oboronlogistika LLC as the sole contractor (for procurement by the russian ministry of defence) for the delivery of troops and cargo by sea ferries to the ТОТ of Crimea and the Kaliningrad region. 
On 14 March 2018, Oboronlogistika LLC started transporting troops and cargo for the Rosgvardia on the ferry routes Ust-Luga port - Baltiysk port and Kavkaz port - Kerch port in accordance with the decision of the russian government.
The Oboronlogistica group of companies includes:
- SK North-West LLC (TIN: 9705070363, under Ukrainian sanctions) is a company whose main activity is shipping in the Baltic Sea and towing on inland waterways, and which has a license to carry out work involving the use of information constituting a state secret and a license to transport dangerous goods by water/sea transport;
- OBL-Shipping LLC (TIN: 9705070412, under Ukrainian sanctions) is a shipping company whose main task is to manage the safe operation of ships, delivery of any type of cargo by inland water and sea transport, including to the facilities of the Arctic zone of the Russian Federation;
- SK-South LLC (TIN: 9705070317, under sanctions of the US, UK, Ukraine) is a company specializing in providing comprehensive freight forwarding services in the Southern Federal District;
- JSC ‘1470 Logistics Management’ (TIN: 7729634801, under Ukrainian sanctions) is a company that provides a full range of services for the responsible storage and handling of goods (including unloading and loading operations, cross-docking, order picking and shipment of goods by groupage wagons, containers, road trains (including shipment of large-sized equipment by rail, platforms). The company also produces furniture and reinforced concrete products, owns warehouses and port terminals throughout russia, and provides services for the shipment of heavy and oversized cargo and special equipment by rail and platforms;
- OBL-Trans LLC (TIN: 5030093611, under Ukrainian sanctions) is a company that organizes road and rail transport and integrates all transport resources of the Oboronlogistika Group into a single chain;
- OBL-SpetsTrans LLC (TIN: 5032299456, under Ukrainian sanctions) is a company that manages road and rail transport, provides forwarding and transport services in special areas, and works with cargo of all categories, including dangerous, oversized and military cargo;
- BID JSC (TIN: 5024224658) - a company that automates freight transport, allowing for efficient planning, dispatching, prompt shipment of goods at the lowest cost and constant monitoring at all stages of transport and logistics services."

"A machine-building company specializing in the development, production and repair of electrical equipment and automatic control systems for russian aircraft.
As part of the cooperation for the production of the Orion UAV:
- manufactures and supplies power control devices for starters and control switchgear for the power supply system;
- participates in the production of computers and steering drives that are part of the ""KSU-Orion"", electric brake drives and electric landing gear release drives, and an electric pulse de-icing system for a polymer-composite airframe.
.";"A machine-building company specializing in the development, production and repair of electrical equipment and automatic control systems for russian aircraft.
As part of the cooperation for the production of the Orion UAV:
- manufactures and supplies power control devices for starters and control switchgear for the power supply system;
- participates in the production of computers and steering drives that are part of the ""KSU-Orion"", ice removal subsystem unit for the airframe (BPUL);
- supplies TEMP systems as part of the BUPT-1E brake drive control unit, brackets, and IMT brake electromechanisms for chassis system."

"A russian enterprise that is a research and development center for scientific and technological research in the field of micro- and nanoelectronics, development and production of semiconductor products. The company carries out research and development work under federal programs of the ministry of industry and trade, the ministry of education, and Roscosmos. The work is carried out within the framework of programs for the development of the element base, the production of integrated circuit crystals in the Foundry mode for partner companies, as well as the development and mastering of series of integrated circuits and semiconductor devices.
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile system it produces and supplies:
- FPGA 556PT2.2112 and buffer inverters 133LN3A.2227 for the BT692-405 board as part of the Zarya-61M onboard digital computer;
- 512PS11.2343 converters and 550UP1.2237 terminal amplifiers for the board from the air pressure measurement system (APMS) unit;
- 4-logic elements 533LA9.1410 and inverters 530LN2.1506 for the KLYV.467562.0029 board from the GIB-123-4 inertial navigation system."

"Russian company, one of the leaders in the market of high-tech aviation and space instrumentation. It has developed production in the following technological areas:
- manufacturing of parts from thermoplastic and thermosetting plastics and rubber-like compounds;
- foundry production of parts made of aluminum and magnesium alloys and steels, equipped with equipment for die casting;
- stamping production, equipped with special and universal hydraulic presses, automatic presses and other specialized equipment;
- production of printed circuit boards using various technological methods.
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile system it produces and supplies GIB-123-4 gyroscopic-inertial units for AB-60IS 9B705 onboard control systems (BCS).
As part of its cooperation in the production of Kh-59M2/Kh-59M2A guided missiles it manufactures and supplies US-K-001-03 guidance devices."

"The company is one of russia's leading developers of integrated control systems, automatic and remote control systems, integrated control systems for airplanes, helicopters of military and civil aviation, and missile technology products.
As part of its cooperation on the production of Orion UAVs the company participates in the production and supply of electric brake actuators and electric chassis release actuators, manufactures and supplies KSU-Orion integrated control systems and their components:
- VDU-263 remote control computers; 
- REMP-17 electromechanical steering drives (including BUP-7 drive control units and IM-18 actuators);
- RZMP-17-01 electromechanical steering drives (including BUP-7-01 drive control units and IM-18 actuators); 
- ShEMP-19 chassis electromechanical drives (includes BUPSh-8 chassis drive control units and IMSh-20 chassis actuators).";"The company is one of russia's leading developers of integrated control systems, automatic and remote control systems, integrated control systems for airplanes, helicopters of military and civil aviation, and missile technology products.
As part of the cooperation for the production of the Orion UAVs, the company is involved in the production and supply of electric brake actuators and electric landing gear release actuators, as well as computers and steering drives that are part of the ""KSU-Orion"" system."

"As the director of the State Historical and Archaeological Reserve ""Chersonesos Tavriya"" (TOT of Ukraine):
- organises illegal archaeological excavations on the territory of the temporarily occupied city of Sevastopol and the Autonomous Republic of Crimea;
- assists with financing archaeological expeditions;
- supports and participates in cultural and scientific conferences, seminars and other events aimed at propaganda and implantation of imperialist narratives. 
- is responsible for the museum's illegal construction on the territory of the UNESCO monument ""The Ancient City of Chersonesos Tavriya and its Chora"" and in its buffer zone."

"The company manufactures microwave units and modules for various purposes, microwave multi-channel receivers for onboard radar systems, and provides repair and post-warranty support for products, including:
- electronic equipment for military aviation;
- single-channel and multi-channel microwave radar receivers for MiG-29, MiG-31, Su-24, Su-27, Su-30MKI aircraft;
- digital multi-channel receivers for onboard radars;
- microwave modules (low-noise amplifiers, generators, frequency converters for ground and airborne radars for various purposes), etc.
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of Orion UAVs it manufactured components (units BL1-32 and BL1-37) of the radar transmitter channel for this UAV (code name: ""UAV radar transmitter channel"")."

"The russian company specializes on the development and production of semiconductor products, including microcontrollers and microprocessors. 
As part of the cooperation on the production of Kh-101 missiles, it produced electronic components, including:
- 1638RR1 integrated circuits, 1637RU1 RAM, 1637RU1AU RAM, H1806HM1 matrices, which are part of the missile's EOM K003 computer block;
- H1537HM1 bmc for 3200 gates, which are part of the onboard digital computer unit ""Baguette 62-04"" of the missile.
As part of the cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile complex it manufactures and supplies:
- ECBs (N1537XM1 bmk for 3200 valves), which are part of the Baget 62-04 BTsOM unit;
- basic matrix crystals 1537ХМ1Т.1741.198 for the BT692-405 board and basic matrix crystals 1806VP1.2428 for the BT62-4066 board, which are components of the Zarya-61M onboard digital computer;
- multifunctional FPGA H1806XM1.2342.061 from the SIVD block board."

"A Belarusian company that covers the full cycle of development and production of integrated circuits and discrete semiconductor devices.
As part of the cooperation on the production of Kh-101 missiles, the company produced, in particular
- 1533SP1 and 1533AP6 integrated circuits, which are part of the missile's VSS-1 control system
- 1533ID7 decoder-demultiplexer 3-8, which are part of the missile's unit ""EVM K003"" ;
- 1533AP3 digital integrated circuits of transistor logic with Schottky diodes of TTL series; 9000RU4U CMOS RAM with information capacity 9000RU4U, which are part of the ""Baguette 62-04"" missile's BCOM unit;
- 588IR1 multifunctional 8-bit buffer registers; 1554TM2T, 1564LN1, 537RU13, 1554LE1T, 588VS2A microcircuits, which are part of the ""Monoblock-L"" missile's block.
As part of the cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile complex it manufactures and supplies:
- 4-bit selectors 1533KP14.2235 and 4-channel formers 2050. 1533AP5 for the BT692-405 board, 4-bit D-type registers 2321.1533IR38 for the BT62-408 board from the Zarya-61M onboard digital computer; 
- 4-bit D-type registers 2321.1533IR38 for the BT62-408 board, 512PS112343 converters, 1950.588VG8T controllers from the air pressure measurement system (SIVD) unit.
As part of cooperation in the production of the Izdelie-30 cruise missile it manufactures eight-bit registers that are part of the BUBS-30 warhead equipment control unit."

"The company is one of the largest russian manufacturers and exporters of microelectronic products. It is the only mass production of microelectronics with a topology of up to 90 nm in russia, part of the Element group of companies, and a resident of the Technopolis Moscow special economic zone. 
As part of the cooperation on the production of Kh-101 missiles, it produced electronic components (169AA1 and 533LL1OSM chips, 572PA2 12-bit multiplier digital-to-analog converters, and 533AP6OSM eight-channel bidirectional converters), which are part of the missile's unit ""EVM K003"".
As part of the cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile complex it manufactures: 
- 556RT2.2112 FPGA and 133LN3A.2227 buffer inverters for the BT692-405 board from the Zarya-61M onboard digital computer; 
- 512PS11.2343 converters and 550UP1.2237 power amplifiers for the board from the air pressure measurement system (SIVD) unit; 
- 4-logic elements 533LA9.1410 and inverters 530LN2.1506 for the KLYV.467562.0029 board from the GIB-123-4 inertial navigation system."

"Part of the Kronshtadt group of companies, which specialises in the development and production of UAVs and cooperates with the russian ministry of defence and the FSB. It is a regular participant in the Army forums. The group's products include Orion, Inokhodets, Molniya, Grom, Termit, Helios, Sirius UAVs and ground control systems.
As part of the cooperation on the production of Orion UAVs:
- supplies combined-type ""BANO"" air navigation lights, which are installed on the fuselage for light marking purposes;
- develops and manufactures ""BUOSO"" general aviation equipment control units and ""BIUS-BLA"" airborne information and control systems with special ""VTs-S"" computers, which are part of airborne electronic computers;
- participates in the supply of ""NIUS"" products, ""BRD"" and ""ASDN"" onboard data recorders;
- participates in the production of digital signal processing units ""TsOS-B"" and antenna-electronic on-board transceiver units ""AEB-B"", which are part of radio-electronic complexes for command and information interaction;
- participates in the production of the ""OES-Obzornaya"" optical-electronic surveillance system and GLONASS/GPS GNSS signal control and correction stations, which are part of the automatic take-off and landing system.";"Specializes in the development of high-tech solutions for robotic systems and a wide range of equipment for unmanned systems (onboard equipment, ground control equipment for UAVs, payloads, etc.). It cooperates with the russian defense ministry and the FSB. Regular participant of the Army forums.
It is a part of the Kronstadt group of companies. The group's products include Orion, Molniya, Grom, Termit, Helios, Sirius UAVs and ground control systems.
As part of the cooperation for the production of the Orion UAVs it:
- develops and manufactures control units for common aircraft equipment ""BUOSO BLA"", onboard information and control systems ""BIUS-BLA"" with special computers ""VC-S"", onboard data recorders ""BRD"" (comprising data storage units and information processing units), ""ASDN"" units, which are part of the UAV's computer system;
- manufactures digital signal processing units ""COS-B"" and antennae-electronic transceiver units ""AEB-B"", which are part of the UAV command and information interaction radio electronic complex;
- manufactures and supplies observation optoelectronic systems ""OES-Obzornaya"" and control and correction stations for GLONASS/GPS signals, which are part of the UAV flight and navigation equipment;
- supplies onboard air navigation lights of the combined type TA-ZSKh and TA-KSKh, which are installed on the UAV body for the purpose of light marking."

"Developer and manufacturer of electronic components for radio-electronic equipment and low-current switching equipment (relays and switches). In particular, it develops actuators for russian satellites and microwave modules for radars. It is part of the state corporation Rostec.
As part of the cooperation on the production of Kh-101 missiles, the company supplies electronic components (relay RPK102V) to NIIHIT JSC for the manufacture of the onboard power supply 25NKM-5-B. Also, it supplies other electronic components (relays ""REA16"", ""REA17"", ""REK80"", ""REK87V isp. 14"") to JSC ""SmAZ"", which can be used in the control circuit of onboard equipment, power distribution, safety and control of the missile.
As part of cooperation in the production of Kh-59M2/Kh-59M2A guided missiles, it supplies ECB:
- REK 87-13, REK 87V-13, REK 87V-18 relays to UAPO JSC for the production of the rectification, regulation and switching unit BVRK-9M2;
- RPK102V and RPK59-V ""7"" relays to NIIKHIT JSC for the manufacture of the 25NKM-5-B on-board power supply;
- relays RPK102V, REA16, REA17 to SmAZ JSC."

"A leading Russian company in the production of printed circuit boards. It provides serial and contract manufacturing of printed circuit boards and modular soldering. It has two factories, three assembly workshops and two stencil sites. The company's production capacity is currently more than 40,000 square metres of PCBs per year, which allows it to produce prototypes, small and medium series of up to 32 layers (including the production of hybrid multilayer PCBs, multilayer PCBs made of high-temperature and microwave materials, HDI, flexible and flexible-rigid PCBs). 
It supplies printed circuit boards for the Russian military-industrial complex, including: 
- JSC NII VEKTOR, which develops UAV countermeasures, electronic warfare and reconnaissance systems, and the Penicillin sound and heat reconnaissance system;
- JSC ANGSTREM, which, among other things, produces electronics for navigation systems used in Russian missiles;
- LLC NPO Izhevsk Unmanned Systems, which specialises in the development, production, repair and maintenance of aircraft and special equipment. It is a part of the Kalashnikov Concern. The company's developments include Takhion, Granat and Supecam UAVs, which are used in the war against Ukraine."

"Specialises in the development, production and modernisation of missiles of various classes. The company's products include Kh-59 and Kh-69 guided missiles, Kh-32 and Kh-101 cruise missiles.
The company is the main contractor of state defence contracts concluded with the russian ministry of defence for the supply of Kh-101 strategic air-launched cruise missiles, participates in the fulfilment of the state defence order for the supply of Kh-59M2/Kh-59M2A guided air missiles. The company's management monitors the progress of state defence orders for its production, in particular:
- holds meetings with the participation of co-operation companies to provide the most demanded equipment and products and approves relevant decisions;
- supervises the conclusion of contracts between the participants of the cooperation;
- checks delivery schedules for key components and equipment;
- organises the resolution of problematic issues, etc. 
In addition to its organisational role, the company is directly involved in the production of Kh-101 missile parts, including the assembly of remote onboard containers for navigation system elements, wing consoles and other structural parts, etc.
As part of its cooperation in the production of Kh-59M2/Kh-59M2A guided missiles, JSC GosMKB Raduga participated in the adoption of the following decisions: on the manufacture, testing and delivery of 9-A-2634 products; the development and completion of duplicate forms for R95TP engines dismantled from D9M and D9M-01 products for their adaptation to D9M2 and D9M2A products; on the use of parts, assemblies and components from BREM-3 blocks from the D9M product warehouse for the assembly of BREM-3 blocks that are part of D9M2A products; on the procedure for manufacturing 9TK1D-00 engines for the assembly of D9M2 products; the procedure for working with R95TP engines dismantled from the D9M product; the organisation of duplicate production of components for T1A-02 and T1B-02 equipment, etc."

"Russian electrical engineering holding company engaged in the construction and reconstruction of electricity distribution systems. Main areas of activity:
- design of power supply systems for energy and industrial facilities;
- production and supply of electrical equipment for 0.4-220 kV, including relay protection equipment, low-voltage and high-voltage equipment, low-voltage switchgear, electric drives, 6-10 kV switchgear, 220 kV open switchgear;
- providing services for installation, commissioning, warranty and maintenance of the supplied electrical equipment;
- performing general contracting works for the construction of power facilities.
As part of the cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile system it manufactures and supplies intermediate relays RNE.31V.27V.N2189346, which are an integral part of the RR-97 switchgear unit board."

"A company that has a full range of modern equipment and technologies from the production of amorphous and nanocrystalline tapes to the packaging of finished electromagnetic components (toroidal magnetic cores, miniature pulse transformers and blocks, high-frequency chokes and transformers for telecommunication systems, low-frequency power transformers, etc.)
Manufacturer and supplier of TIS2-3 transformers, which are part of the onboard equipment of the S8000 ""Banderol"" cruise missile.
As part of the cooperation on the production of Kh-101 missiles, the company produced the following electrical components:
- BTI3-61V pulse transformer units, which are part of the missile's UVK-208 unit;
- TIL6V linear pulse transformers, which are part of the Baget 62-04 missile's onboard digital computer.
Within the framework of cooperation on the production of the 9M727 cruise missile from the Iskander-K missile system it produces and supplies the following ECBs:
- linear pulse transformers TIL6V, which are part of the Baget 62-04 and Zarya-61M missile's onboard digital computers;
- transformers BTI8-52V.2211 for the BT62-408 board from the ""Zarya-61M"" onboard digital computer;
- transformers BTI6-109V.2308 for the KLYV.468151.031-01 board from the GIB-123-4 inertial navigation system."

"A russian company that develops and manufactures control systems for launch vehicles and spacecraft. The main areas of work are:
- creation of control computer systems (UVK), instruments and software for launch vehicles and upper stages;
- development of ground and on-board equipment for satellite systems such as GLONASS, creation of civilian navigators under the Glospace brand;
- development and support of software and mathematical models for ground testing of onboard devices of spacecraft;
- manufacture and supply of telemetry equipment for upper stages. 
The Institute is a branch of the United Rocket and Space Corporation, a part of the Roscosmos State Corporation.
As part of the cooperation on the production of 9M723 ballistic missiles, Iskander-M produces and supplies 9B919 receiving and processing units."

"In accordance with his official duties, the Director of the Federal State Budgetary Institution of Culture of the russian federation ""State Hermitage"" M. B. Piotrovsky: 
- implements the state targeted programmes of the russian federation, which include archaeological work in the occupied territories of Ukraine and the illegal transfer of Ukrainian cultural property;
- provides mandatory cover letters to scientists (representatives of the Hermitage) in order to obtain open letters for archaeological work in the occupied territories of Ukraine;
- Provides funding and other logistical support for the activities of expeditions and individual Hermitage staff in the occupied territory of Ukraine. 
As the director of the Hermitage, from 2014 to 2023, Piotrovsky facilitated the receipt of at least 53 open letters for employees to conduct archaeological work in the occupied territory of Ukraine."
